===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[increase]]; to make [[large|larger]] or [[supplement]].
#: ''The money from renting out a spare room can '''augment''' a salary.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive|reflexive}} To [[grow]]; to increase; to become [[greater]].
# {{lb|en|music}} To [[slow]] the [[tempo]] or [[meter]], e.g. for a dramatic or stately passage.
# {{lb|en|music}} To increase an [[interval]], especially the largest interval in a [[triad]], by a half [[step]] ([[chromatic]] [[semitone]]).
# {{lb|en|grammar|transitive}} To add an augment to.

